HEADWORD: Pneumatograph
<hw>Pneu*mat"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pneumato-</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for recording the movements of
the thorax or chest wall during respiration; -- also called
<altname>stethograph</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pneumatological</ent>⟦br⟧
